``` ::: ::: ::: ::: {.callout-note icon="false"} ## Full Methodology The full methodology for how these scores are calculated and why they are important for consideration in upzoning is [available in the full report](../quarto/report_shiny.html). ::: ## Service Frequency Service frequency is calculated as the mean number of services per hour in two periods of travel: - Between 7 and 10am towards Flinders Street, shown in blue. - Between 4 and 7pm away from Flinders Street, shown in green. :::{.graph} ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: ::: column-margin The chart is also split by direction of travel, which in Melbourne's radial network is either towards or away from Flinders street. \ The mean values of these two periods are shown as dashed lines, and the mean of those two numbers is the final score. ::: \ Union has a morning frequency of 7.27 and an evening frequency of 6.36. The raw value is therefore **6.81** ## Available Line Capacity ::: {.cell} ::: The chart below shows the average patronage on the Belgrave, Lilydale line(s) at the last stop before the CBD (Richmond). It is calculated for the same travel times as [#service-frequency] above. :::{.graph} ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: \ Union has an average morning service patronage of 339.31 and an average evening patronage of 317.46. The raw value is **328.38.** :::{.callout-note} Higher patronage value means lower line capacity score, reflected in the table at the top of this page and throughout this report. ::: ## Existing Transport Infrastructure ::: {.cell} ::: The map below shows tram routes and tram stops in green, as well as bus routes and bus stops in orange. ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: \ There are 4 tram stops in a 1km radius, with route(s) 109 servicing the area. For buses, there are 31, with route(s) 612, 766, 284. The data below shows the frequencies per route, split by mode. ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ::: ::: {.cell .column-page layout-nrow="1"} ::: The final transport connections score is computed by summing the average frequencies of each route and applying a weight to each mode. Tram routes are given twice the weight of bus routes. The final raw value of Union transport connections is **19.66**. ## Zoning Suitability The map below shows the properties within 1km of Union that are suitable for upzoning in dark green, with unsuitable properties in dark gray ::: column-margin Suitable properties are either neighbourhood residential or general residential and not under heritage restrictions. ::: ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: \ Out of 3937 lots within 1000m radius of Union, 2652 are suitable for upzoning. In terms of area, the most suitable properties cover **58**% of the total area. For more information, see the table below. :::{.graph} ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: ## Local Amenities The map below shows the local amenities near Union within a 1000m radius. ::: {.callout-caution collapse="true"} ## Notes on Data Visualisation OpenStreetMap point locations were joined to polygon dwelling data for this visualisation. Some points could not be joined and are displayed as circles on the map. Some amenities are within the same building, e.g. multiple shops in shopping centres. In these cases, the building is assigned a colour corresponding to the most common amenity within it. ::: ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: \ The plot below visualises the number of local services within the station catchment. Data is drawn from OpenStreetMaps classifications. The black dotted lines represent the average for each category across all stations included in the model. :::{.graph} ::: {.cell} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: Calculation of the final score for local services uses an index measure. It is described in more detail [in the full report](../quarto/report_shiny.html). ## Distance to CBD Union is 1.170396\times 10^{4} metres from Flinders Street Station, as the crow flies. ___ To learn more about these metrics and their calculation, visit the [report methodology](../quarto/report_shiny.html). :::{.graph} ::: {.cell} ::: :::
